\SE[2]I have my own room too, but... \SE[54]I think I prefer
spending time here with everyone... Maybe...

\SE[68]...As for Vega, you know... \SE[66]She drinks a lot
of water while studying, so she goes to the bathroom
frequently.

\SE\SE[52]...Even if it's tough, don't bear it alone.
\!\SE[57]We feel the same way too... So \!\SE[52]I think you
already understand that without me having to say it now.

\SE[2]There have been various things... But... \SE[18]As
long as everyone is smiling, that's what makes me the
happiest...

It seems like Vita is preparing a stew. It's said to be a
specialty of the Hajikko Village and it's very delicious.

Cooking is done on a rotation basis. I am the second best at
cooking. The first place is overwhelmingly held by Vita.
Well, the cooking of those two...

It's been there from the beginning, 'alcohol.' It seems like
a 'good thing,' but no one can drink it... What should I
do...

It's a dish made by Ulyssean. It seems to have a good
reputation for its high quality. Honestly, I can't tell the
difference though.

There are everyone's favorite juices placed here. Each one
has a 'name tag' hanging from it.
If you accidentally drink the wrong one, it'll be war. War.
Vega has stored water. It's a lot. Too much.

It's a night light... Vega, who often wakes up to go to the
bathroom, uses it the most.

Yurisine's vegetables taste delicious. But I think the sweet
potatoes from Hatayaki Village were even more delicious...

The rule is not to leave dishes unwashed. If you break it,
Lunaroa won't talk to you for the whole day. It's tough.
It's lonely.

Burning gas to ignite the fire, it's the latest kitchen.
Luna Roa and Vega use magic to cook, so only Vita and I are
the ones who use it.
